00:45:10.377 --> 00:45:13.380
BECKET: <i>But Steven Redfellow</i>
<i>had no shortage of enemies.</i>

943
00:45:13.480 --> 00:45:14.516
<i>The man had been indicted</i>

944
00:45:14.616 --> 00:45:16.050
<i>in two different countries</i>
<i>for money laundering.</i>

945
00:45:16.150 --> 00:45:17.718
<i>and let's not forget</i>
<i>the lawsuit</i>

946
00:45:17.818 --> 00:45:19.420
<i>with his former</i>
<i>business manager.</i>

947
00:45:19.521 --> 00:45:20.888
The crossroads. yet again.

948
00:45:20.988 --> 00:45:23.791
BECKET: <i>So if Steven ended up</i>
<i>in a dumpster somewhere...</i>

949
00:45:24.892 --> 00:45:26.894
<i>perhaps</i>
<i>it would be God's will.</i>

950
00:45:26.994 --> 00:45:29.063
(CHRISTIAN ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

951
00:45:30.699 --> 00:45:33.668
STEVEN: ...dicking us around.
Yeah.

952
00:45:33.767 --> 00:45:35.436
Look. nobody doesn't
call you for three days

953
00:45:35.537 --> 00:45:37.171
and thinks you're
a priority. okay?

954
00:45:38.205 --> 00:45:41.509
No. No. they're
pulling our leg. man.

955
00:45:42.611 --> 00:45:45.145
Oh. Mmm-hmm.

956
00:45:46.548 --> 00:45:48.949
Yeah. that's 'cause
they're in real estate. Jason.

957
00:45:49.049 --> 00:45:50.217
All right. look.
Uh. I gotta bounce.

958
00:45:50.317 --> 00:45:51.885
I will hit you back later.
all right?

959
00:45:51.986 --> 00:45:53.320
All right. peace.

960
00:45:53.420 --> 00:45:58.492
Whoo! I just get so fricken
hyped on first Sundays. right?

961
00:45:58.593 --> 00:45:59.860
-Oh. come on.
-Oh.

962
00:45:59.960 --> 00:46:01.630
Ben Johnson.
<i>Midwest Christian Magazine.</i>

963
00:46:01.730 --> 00:46:04.131
Oh. come on.
I know who you are. Please.

964
00:46:04.231 --> 00:46:05.899
Have a seat.

965
00:46:06.000 --> 00:46:07.835
Look. I'm sorry we couldn't
sit down last month.

966
00:46:07.935 --> 00:46:09.303
I was actually in Korea.

967
00:46:09.403 --> 00:46:10.871
We're opening a church over
there. so it's exciting stuff.

968
00:46:10.971 --> 00:46:12.873
-Korea?
-It's a magical place.

969
00:46:12.973 --> 00:46:14.275
Magical people.

970
00:46:14.375 --> 00:46:17.878
Complicated tax laws. so...
(CHUCKLES)

971
00:46:17.978 --> 00:46:19.413
I think our readers
just want to know

972
00:46:19.514 --> 00:46:20.515
the man behind the movement.

973
00:46:21.650 --> 00:46:22.783
Let's do it!

974
00:46:22.883 --> 00:46:23.851
Let's do it.

975
00:46:23.951 --> 00:46:25.286
Uh. you want to start
with the photos?

976
00:46:25.386 --> 00:46:26.755
-Sure. Yeah.
-Um...

977
00:46:26.854 --> 00:46:28.188
Can you tell me about
this one right here?

978
00:46:28.289 --> 00:46:31.225
Okay. Uh. that's me
and the President of Armenia.

979
00:46:31.325 --> 00:46:33.127
President of Panama. Look.
the church has been lucky

980
00:46:33.227 --> 00:46:34.962
to make some good friends
over the years.

981
00:46:35.062 --> 00:46:37.732
That is me with El Chapo.

982
00:46:37.831 --> 00:46:40.434
Super interesting dude
if you actually.

983
00:46:40.535 --> 00:46:42.303
I don't know. talk to him.

984
00:46:42.403 --> 00:46:43.437
I mean... (CHUCKLES)

985
00:46:43.538 --> 00:46:46.741
But the press barbequed me
for that one too.

986
00:46:46.840 --> 00:46:48.142
I'm not sure
if you know this. but...

987
00:46:49.476 --> 00:46:52.446
I'm from like a. kind of
a well-known family.

988
00:46:53.947 --> 00:46:54.948
I don't know. It just means
people are always

989
00:46:55.049 --> 00:46:56.016
trying to knock me down.

990
00:46:56.116 --> 00:46:57.619
You know.
take me out the game.

991
00:46:57.719 --> 00:46:59.019
I just always tell myself

992
00:46:59.119 --> 00:47:00.054
it's nothing my buddy J.C.

993
00:47:00.154 --> 00:47:01.623
didn't have
to deal with. right?

994
00:47:01.723 --> 00:47:03.123
It's. like. don't hate on me

995
00:47:03.223 --> 00:47:04.693
just 'cause
my dad's a big deal.

996
00:47:04.793 --> 00:47:06.060
or whatever. right?

997
00:47:06.160 --> 00:47:07.127
Amen.

998
00:47:07.227 --> 00:47:08.896
STEVEN: Yeah. you get it.
You know who else got it?

999
00:47:08.996 --> 00:47:10.431
Mayor of Kyoto.

1000
00:47:11.298 --> 00:47:13.334
God put it on my heart
to open a church there. too.

1001
00:47:13.434 --> 00:47:14.736
And he gave me this. Oh.

1002
00:47:14.835 --> 00:47:15.936
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)
Look at that.

1003
00:47:16.036 --> 00:47:17.137
(STEVEN MIMICS SWORD SWISHING)

1004
00:47:17.237 --> 00:47:19.006
Whoa. whoa. whoa. (CHUCKLES)

1005
00:47:20.174 --> 00:47:22.009
-Ooh-ah!
-(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

1006
00:47:22.109 --> 00:47:24.579
Here. feel it. Feel the tip.
Feel how sharp that is.

1007
00:47:26.280 --> 00:47:27.515
Feel it. Come on.
You gotta feel it.

1008
00:47:27.615 --> 00:47:28.616
Okay. (CLEARS THROAT)

1009
00:47:28.717 --> 00:47:29.850
That's it. just touch it.

1010
00:47:29.950 --> 00:47:32.486
-Wow. Ow. (CHUCKLES)
-STEVEN: Right? (LAUGHS)

1011
00:47:32.587 --> 00:47:34.589
STEVEN: Yeah. it's. like.
razor sharp. right?

1012
00:47:34.689 --> 00:47:36.056
So sharp.

1013
00:47:36.156 --> 00:47:37.592
I can give you a shave from
all the way over here. right?

1014
00:47:37.692 --> 00:47:39.393
Well. I shaved
this morning. so...

1015
00:47:43.897 --> 00:47:45.099
I know it was you.

1016
00:47:48.402 --> 00:47:49.970
I knew it was you
before you walked in the door.

1017
00:47:50.070 --> 00:47:52.473
See. Ben Johnson retired
eight months ago. so...

1018
00:47:54.108 --> 00:47:55.275
Your other victims
might've been too dumb

1019
00:47:55.376 --> 00:47:57.478
to put it together.
but not me.

1020
00:47:58.546 --> 00:48:00.314
You don't get out of here
until you come clean.

1021
00:48:02.116 --> 00:48:03.283
Come clean? What?

1022
00:48:03.384 --> 00:48:04.918
STEVEN: Come on.
Come on. let me hear it.

1023
00:48:05.018 --> 00:48:06.353
BECKET: Hear what?
What... what do you want?

1024
00:48:06.453 --> 00:48:08.222
The truth. Come on.

1025
00:48:08.857 --> 00:48:10.157
You gotta
let that shit out. Right?

1026
00:48:10.257 --> 00:48:11.726
Look. I think you have me
confused with someone else.

1027
00:48:11.826 --> 00:48:13.828
-I know everything! Say it!
-(YELPS)

1028
00:48:13.927 --> 00:48:14.995
(HESITATES)
What do you want me to say?

1029
00:48:15.095 --> 00:48:16.296
-What do you want me to say?
-Give it to me!

1030
00:48:16.397 --> 00:48:18.566
-Come on! Come on!
-Hey! Okay. okay. okay. okay.

1031
00:48:18.666 --> 00:48:21.135
Get it out there in the air.
Exorcise that shit!

1032
00:48:21.235 --> 00:48:22.604
Okay. okay. okay.
I lied. I lied. I lied.

1033
00:48:22.704 --> 00:48:24.706
-I'm not Ben Johnson. Okay.
-STEVEN: You're not. are you?

1034
00:48:24.806 --> 00:48:26.106
-Who are you?
-I'm Becket. I'm Becket.

1035
00:48:26.206 --> 00:48:27.842
I'm... I'm your cousin!

1036
00:48:27.941 --> 00:48:29.476
(UPBEAT MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS)

1037
00:48:33.848 --> 00:48:35.082
(MUSIC STOPS)

1038
00:48:35.182 --> 00:48:36.383
What'd you just say?

1039
00:48:37.752 --> 00:48:38.919
I'm your...

1040
00:48:39.821 --> 00:48:41.021
I'm... I'm your cousin.

1041
00:48:42.624 --> 00:48:44.224
You're not from <i>The Post?</i>

1042
00:48:44.324 --> 00:48:45.459
You're not
writing a hit piece?

1043
00:48:45.560 --> 00:48:46.561
You're not that guy?

1044
00:48:49.764 --> 00:48:50.931
What?

1045
00:48:53.635 --> 00:48:54.602
Oh.

1046
00:48:55.804 --> 00:48:58.939
(LAUGHS AWKWARDLY) Okay.

1047
00:48:59.039 --> 00:49:02.142
Uh. this is embarrassing.
(CHUCKLES)

1048
00:49:02.242 --> 00:49:05.379
I just get so paranoid
with this job. you know?

1049
00:49:05.479 --> 00:49:07.347
It's... Whew!

1050
00:49:07.816 --> 00:49:08.917
Whew!

1051
00:49:09.016 --> 00:49:11.920
Oh. man. I shoulda known
we were family.

1052
00:49:12.019 --> 00:49:13.521
It's like looking
in a freakin' mirror.

1053
00:49:14.388 --> 00:49:16.390
(SLURPING)

1054
00:49:17.759 --> 00:49:19.727
(EXHALES) Something's
a little off with that.

1055
00:49:21.495 --> 00:49:23.698
BECKET: <i>Did you know</i>
<i>that tropane alkaloids</i>

1056
00:49:23.798 --> 00:49:24.766
<i>are an active ingredient</i>

1057
00:49:24.866 --> 00:49:26.668
<i>in most pre-workout</i>
<i>supplements?</i>

1058
00:49:28.035 --> 00:49:29.102
<i>If you have</i>
<i>too much of the stuff.</i>

1059
00:49:29.203 --> 00:49:30.738
<i>you might have</i>
<i>a massive heart attack.</i>

1060
00:49:31.573 --> 00:49:32.640
(BELL TOLLS)

1061
00:49:32.740 --> 00:49:36.276
BECKET: <i>And by too much.</i>
<i>I mean about 1.500 milligrams.</i>

1062
00:49:36.376 --> 00:49:40.615
And the last thing the church
wanted was an investigation.

1063
00:49:40.715 --> 00:49:42.449
I'm sure
you know all about that.

1064
00:49:43.685 --> 00:49:45.285
Anyway...

1065
00:49:45.385 --> 00:49:47.589
(POIGNANT PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

1066
00:49:49.824 --> 00:49:52.259
<i>Finally.</i>
<i>I was getting somewhere.</i>

1067
00:49:55.062 --> 00:49:56.230
<i>Wasn't I?</i>

1068
00:49:57.599 --> 00:50:00.768
MARY: <i>Promise me</i>
<i>that you won't quit.</i>

1069
00:50:02.737 --> 00:50:05.773
<i>Not until you have</i>
<i>the right kind of life.</i>

1070
00:50:07.976 --> 00:50:10.110
(POIGNANT PIANO MUSIC
CONTINUES)

1071
00:50:29.396 --> 00:50:30.197
(LAUGHS)

1072
00:50:30.297 --> 00:50:31.498
RUTH: <i>Can you keep a secret?</i>

1073
00:50:33.500 --> 00:50:35.369
BECKET: Surprisingly well.
actually.

1074
00:50:37.170 --> 00:50:39.373
I was gonna break up with him
that weekend.

1075
00:50:42.042 --> 00:50:43.845
And now he's gone. and I know

1076
00:50:43.945 --> 00:50:46.146
I'm supposed to feel.
like. devastated

1077
00:50:46.246 --> 00:50:48.550
but I... I don't...
I don't. (SIGHS)

1078
00:50:48.650 --> 00:50:52.720
No. You feel what
you're supposed to feel.

1079
00:50:55.924 --> 00:50:57.792
Does that make me
a terrible person?

1080
00:50:57.892 --> 00:50:59.126
No.

1081
00:51:00.093 --> 00:51:01.529
I think it makes you honest.

1082
00:51:05.432 --> 00:51:07.501
I don't know. I think
I'm still going to hell.

1083
00:51:07.602 --> 00:51:09.571
-(CHUCKLES)
-Man. you're talking to a guy

1084
00:51:09.671 --> 00:51:10.437
who works on Wall Street.

1085
00:51:10.538 --> 00:51:13.273
RUTH: Oh. you're
definitely going to hell.

1086
00:51:13.373 --> 00:51:14.976
Do you want to grab dinner
this week?

1087
00:51:15.075 --> 00:51:17.177
Yes. (LAUGHS)

1088
00:51:17.277 --> 00:51:20.147
Um. my office can grab us
a reservation at The Modern.

1089
00:51:20.247 --> 00:51:22.517
Uh. it's midtown. Um...

1090
00:51:22.617 --> 00:51:24.519
I've never been there.
but I hear it's great.

1091
00:51:24.619 --> 00:51:26.054
Yeah.

1092
00:51:26.153 --> 00:51:30.490
Or we could keep it simple
and cook something?

1093
00:51:31.993 --> 00:51:34.461
Yeah. simple. I love simple.

1094
00:51:48.676 --> 00:51:49.844
(MUSIC STOPS)

1095
00:51:50.712 --> 00:51:51.679
(BECKET EXHALES)

1096
00:51:52.379 --> 00:51:54.749
I know. Dramatic. right?

1097
00:51:54.849 --> 00:51:55.850
What are you doing?

1098
00:51:55.950 --> 00:51:57.184
JULIA: What are you doing?

1099
00:51:57.752 --> 00:51:59.252
We had an agreement.

1100
00:51:59.353 --> 00:52:01.923
First off. how did you
get in my apartment?

1101
00:52:02.023 --> 00:52:03.625
I took a key
right in front of you.

1102
00:52:04.291 --> 00:52:05.660
No. I remember.

1103
00:52:06.326 --> 00:52:09.864
Two calls. two emails.
nothing back?

1104
00:52:11.032 --> 00:52:12.667
-I've been occupied.
-JULIA: With what?

1105
00:52:13.835 --> 00:52:14.802
Occupations.

1106
00:52:17.038 --> 00:52:18.238
Go on.

1107
00:52:25.680 --> 00:52:27.247
Come on.

1108
00:52:27.347 --> 00:52:29.282
How long have
we known each other?

1109
00:52:29.383 --> 00:52:30.752
-Quite some time.
-JULIA: So you should

1110
00:52:30.852 --> 00:52:31.886
be able to tell me anything.

1111
00:52:33.153 --> 00:52:34.321
I'll go first.

1112
00:52:35.123 --> 00:52:36.090
We're flat broke.

1113
00:52:36.189 --> 00:52:37.125
My husband
lied to me for years.

1114
00:52:37.257 --> 00:52:38.826
and he's an absolute coward.

1115
00:52:39.627 --> 00:52:40.995
Now you go.

1116
00:52:41.095 --> 00:52:42.664
I have nothing to tell you.

1117
00:52:42.764 --> 00:52:43.731
I would never judge.

1118
00:52:44.932 --> 00:52:45.900
BECKET: For what?

1119
00:52:57.712 --> 00:53:00.515
Well. that would sour things
between us. wouldn't it?

1120
00:53:04.052 --> 00:53:05.252
I don't like it sour.

1121
00:53:08.388 --> 00:53:09.557
I like it sweet.

1122
00:53:10.658 --> 00:53:11.759
(DOORBELL RINGS)

1123
00:53:13.795 --> 00:53:15.530
Oh. my God. Julia. I'm s...
(CLEARS THROAT)

1124
00:53:15.630 --> 00:53:16.698
-JULIA: What?
-You have to go.

1125
00:53:16.798 --> 00:53:18.099
JULIA: Are you
fucking kidding me?

1126
00:53:18.198 --> 00:53:19.534
-I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
-JULIA: What the hell?

1127
00:53:19.634 --> 00:53:20.635
I'm sorry.

1128
00:53:21.903 --> 00:53:22.870
You've gotta go.

1129
00:53:29.143 --> 00:53:30.912
-Hey.
-Hi.

1130
00:53:32.580 --> 00:53:35.183
It's a bit of a culinary
disaster in there.

1131
00:53:35.282 --> 00:53:39.587
Oh. Uh. oh. no. (LAUGHS)
Everything okay or...?

1132
00:53:39.687 --> 00:53:41.656
Uh. do you want
to go out to eat?

1133
00:53:41.756 --> 00:53:42.724
Yeah. sure.

1134
00:53:42.824 --> 00:53:43.791
Great.

1135
00:53:45.292 --> 00:53:46.561
(RUTH LAUGHS)

1136
00:53:46.661 --> 00:53:48.863
These students.
I love them. but...

1137
00:53:48.963 --> 00:53:49.764
Tell me about it.

1138
00:53:49.864 --> 00:53:51.132
RUTH: They all want
to be millionaires.

1139
00:53:51.231 --> 00:53:54.102
but none of them
want an actual job.

1140
00:53:54.202 --> 00:53:56.037
BECKET: They all gotta
have a dream. right?

1141
00:53:56.137 --> 00:53:58.539
-I get it. but...
-Thank you.

1142
00:53:58.940 --> 00:54:00.340
Thank you.

1143
00:54:03.945 --> 00:54:04.912
I mean. I think it's...

1144
00:54:05.713 --> 00:54:07.447
I think it's good
to want more.

1145
00:54:08.348 --> 00:54:10.752
Okay. gun to your head.

1146
00:54:10.852 --> 00:54:12.553
What would you even do
with a billion dollars?

1147
00:54:12.653 --> 00:54:13.855
Why do you have
a gun to my head?

1148
00:54:13.955 --> 00:54:14.756
Answer the question.

1149
00:54:14.856 --> 00:54:16.557
Get those chopstick guns
out of my face.

1150
00:54:16.657 --> 00:54:18.192
(LAUGHS) Answer the question.

1151
00:54:18.291 --> 00:54:19.794
-I don't know.
-(RUTH CHUCKLES)

1152
00:54:22.295 --> 00:54:23.765
I'd take you
to a better restaurant.

1153
00:54:23.865 --> 00:54:28.836
Working in fashion
was my lifelong goal. right?

1154
00:54:28.936 --> 00:54:30.671
Like. I had tunnel vision.

1155
00:54:30.772 --> 00:54:35.176
And now all I can think about
is the time I put in.

1156
00:54:35.275 --> 00:54:39.312
What. uh. we shouldn't
chase what we want?

1157
00:54:39.412 --> 00:54:42.349
The thing is.
I think I knew the whole time.

1158
00:54:42.449 --> 00:54:44.619
-Knew what?
-That I didn't like it.

1159
00:54:45.653 --> 00:54:48.089
That I might be happier
making shit money

1160
00:54:48.189 --> 00:54:50.390
and having a cactus garden.

1161
00:54:52.693 --> 00:54:55.997
It's just scary
to dream small.

1162
00:54:57.397 --> 00:54:59.066
Nobody teaches us
how to do that.

1163
00:55:01.569 --> 00:55:02.637
FATHER MORRIS: <i>Uh. sorry. I...</i>

1164
00:55:02.737 --> 00:55:04.105
<i>I don't mean</i>
<i>to interrupt. but...</i>

1165
00:55:04.205 --> 00:55:06.439
at this point.
you met someone.

1166
00:55:07.141 --> 00:55:08.441
you had a good career.

1167
00:55:09.143 --> 00:55:10.678
Was that not enough?

1168
00:55:12.146 --> 00:55:13.313
Enough what?

1169
00:55:18.686 --> 00:55:19.754
Look...

1170
00:55:21.022 --> 00:55:22.389
<i>It wasn't lost on me.</i>

1171
00:55:22.489 --> 00:55:25.092
<i>I had a good job.</i>
<i>a budding romance.</i>

1172
00:55:25.193 --> 00:55:26.426
<i>Maybe I should hit pause</i>

1173
00:55:26.527 --> 00:55:29.462
<i>on the systematic killing</i>
<i>of my entire family.</i>

1174
00:55:29.564 --> 00:55:31.398
Reservation at Manilla's.
Friday?

1175
00:55:31.498 --> 00:55:33.067
Friday? Get outta here.

1176
00:55:33.167 --> 00:55:34.235
-(VOICEMAIL BEEPS)
-No way.

1177
00:55:34.334 --> 00:55:35.303
JULIA: <i>Becket. it's me again.</i>

1178
00:55:35.402 --> 00:55:37.138
<i>And you're not answering...</i>
<i>again.</i>

1179
00:55:37.238 --> 00:55:38.573
<i>I wouldn't ignore me</i>
<i>much longer.</i>

1180
00:55:38.673 --> 00:55:40.741
<i>Something bad might happen.</i>
muchacho.

1181
00:55:40.842 --> 00:55:42.210
BECKET: <i>But how</i>
<i>could I quit now?</i>

1182
00:55:42.310 --> 00:55:45.913
<i>I mean. not even one had been</i>
<i>investigated as a murder.</i>

1183
00:55:46.814 --> 00:55:47.915
<i>Was I that good?</i>

1184
00:55:49.517 --> 00:55:50.985
<i>Maybe I was that good.</i>

1185
00:55:51.085 --> 00:55:52.019
<i>Of course. by this point.</i>

1186
00:55:52.119 --> 00:55:54.322
<i>the family had realized</i>
<i>that something was up.</i>

1187
00:55:54.421 --> 00:55:55.556
-(CHILDREN LAUGHING)
-INTERVIEWER: CEO.

1188
00:55:55.656 --> 00:55:57.525
And now. adoption icon.

1189
00:55:57.625 --> 00:55:58.993
BECKET:
<i>Take my Aunt Cassandra.</i>

1190
00:55:59.093 --> 00:56:01.662
<i>She had gotten sort of famous</i>
<i>for adopting. like. 11 kids</i>

1191
00:56:01.762 --> 00:56:03.097
<i>from 11 different countries</i>

1192
00:56:03.197 --> 00:56:05.365
<i>and they spoke 11 different</i>
<i>languages around the house.</i>

1193
00:56:05.465 --> 00:56:06.667
(CHILDREN CLAMORING)

1194
00:56:06.767 --> 00:56:10.104
Okay. I am on the phone.
We can see that. right?

1195
00:56:10.204 --> 00:56:11.505
Do we know phone.

1196
00:56:11.606 --> 00:56:13.674
or do I need to tattoo it
on my fucking forehead?

1197
00:56:13.774 --> 00:56:15.375
BECKET: <i>She heard about</i>
<i>the deaths in the family</i>

1198
00:56:15.475 --> 00:56:17.511
<i>and got a laser-based security</i>
<i>system installed</i>

1199
00:56:17.612 --> 00:56:19.580
<i>in all four of her houses.</i>

1200
00:56:19.680 --> 00:56:21.249
<i>But there wasn't</i>
<i>a security system</i>

1201
00:56:21.349 --> 00:56:23.317
<i>at the Blessings</i>
<i>of the Desert Day Spa</i>

1202
00:56:23.416 --> 00:56:25.519
<i>where she spent</i>
<i>every Tuesday afternoon.</i>

1203
00:56:25.620 --> 00:56:26.821
I'm sorry to disturb you.

1204
00:56:26.921 --> 00:56:29.657
We're offering complimentary
teeth whitening services

1205
00:56:29.757 --> 00:56:32.492
until 5 o'clock.
if you're interested.

1206
00:56:32.593 --> 00:56:34.662
I have some literature
on the process.

1207
00:56:34.762 --> 00:56:35.763
safety information.
if you'd like.

1208
00:56:35.863 --> 00:56:37.131
CASSANDRA: I didn't
come here to read.

1209
00:56:41.102 --> 00:56:42.402
Blessings.

1210
00:56:42.502 --> 00:56:45.740
<i>The special ingredient</i>
<i>was carbamide peroxide</i>

1211
00:56:45.840 --> 00:56:47.208
<i>which is so close</i>
<i>to the acidic agent</i>

1212
00:56:47.308 --> 00:56:48.441
<i>found in teeth whitener</i>

1213
00:56:48.542 --> 00:56:49.877
<i>that the police thought</i>
<i>she must have bought</i>

1214
00:56:49.977 --> 00:56:50.912
<i>an off-brand batch</i>

1215
00:56:51.012 --> 00:56:53.114
<i>during her last adoption trip</i>
<i>to Cambodia.</i>

1216
00:56:53.214 --> 00:56:55.049
(CASSANDRA SPEAKING. MUFFLED)

1217
00:56:55.883 --> 00:56:58.619
-(BELL TOLLS)
-(DUCKS QUACKING)

1218
00:56:58.719 --> 00:57:00.922
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

1219
00:57:05.626 --> 00:57:06.928
BECKET: <i>Then there's</i>
<i>my Uncle McArthur.</i>

1220
00:57:07.028 --> 00:57:08.763
Sir. you've got about
a 30-knot wind

1221
00:57:08.863 --> 00:57:10.497
coming out
of the north-northwest.

1222
00:57:10.598 --> 00:57:11.799
-Just so you know.
-Thanks. but I think

1223
00:57:11.899 --> 00:57:14.268
I can handle
some goddamn wind. chief.

1224
00:57:14.368 --> 00:57:15.502
BECKET: <i>This guy owned. like.</i>

1225
00:57:15.603 --> 00:57:17.038
<i>half The National Air</i>
<i>and Space Museum.</i>

1226
00:57:17.138 --> 00:57:18.773
<i>And while the rest of us</i>
<i>were planning</i>

1227
00:57:18.873 --> 00:57:20.141
<i>a long weekend at Key West.</i>

1228
00:57:20.241 --> 00:57:24.812
<i>he was planning an actual</i>
<i>trip to the actual moon.</i>

1229
00:57:24.912 --> 00:57:26.847
JOURNALIST: McArthur.
what do you say to the critics

1230
00:57:26.948 --> 00:57:29.884
who see you spending
$50 million to fly to space

1231
00:57:29.984 --> 00:57:32.086
when half your employees
don't have health insurance?

1232
00:57:32.186 --> 00:57:34.655
Fifty? More like ninety.

1233
00:57:34.755 --> 00:57:38.225
Look. if I could do this kind
of thing for cheap. I would.

1234
00:57:38.326 --> 00:57:40.493
But it's incredibly expensive.

1235
00:57:40.594 --> 00:57:41.829
-Gassed up?
-ASSISTANT: Yes. sir.

1236
00:57:41.929 --> 00:57:43.331
MCARTHUR: Spot check?
ASSISTANT: Yes. sir.

1237
00:57:43.431 --> 00:57:44.598
MCARTHUR: Where's my coffee.
by the way?

1238
00:57:44.699 --> 00:57:45.967
BECKET: Here you go.

1239
00:57:47.435 --> 00:57:48.636
Lock and load.

1240
00:57:48.736 --> 00:57:50.237
BECKET: <i>All it took</i>
<i>was a laminated pass</i>

1241
00:57:50.338 --> 00:57:51.906
<i>and a shirt from the mall.</i>

1242
00:57:52.006 --> 00:57:53.874
(ALARM BLARING)

1243
00:57:54.842 --> 00:57:58.478
MAN: (OVER RADIO) <i>Charlie 17.</i>
<i>you are very low. over.</i>

1244
00:57:58.579 --> 00:57:59.613
(BELL TOLLS)

1245
00:57:59.714 --> 00:58:02.850
1.500 square feet.
three bedrooms. doorman.

1246
00:58:02.950 --> 00:58:05.353
You ever have
a doorman before?

1247
00:58:05.453 --> 00:58:07.088
-I barely had a door.
-(REALTOR CHUCKLES)

1248
00:58:07.188 --> 00:58:09.724
REALTOR: It changes your life.
I'm not even joking around.

1249
00:58:09.824 --> 00:58:12.560
This is original marble
from. uh. Italy.

1250
00:58:12.660 --> 00:58:13.728
And if you look out there.

1251
00:58:13.828 --> 00:58:15.663
that's what you pay
the money for.

1252
00:58:22.970 --> 00:58:24.205
So would you
want to live here?

1253
00:58:25.673 --> 00:58:26.807
(VEHICLE HONKS)

1254
00:58:26.907 --> 00:58:27.908
With me?

1255
00:58:29.810 --> 00:58:33.714
I know
it's a little fast. but...

1256
00:58:34.982 --> 00:58:37.184
I'd really
like to have you here.

1257
00:58:39.286 --> 00:58:40.888
I'd love it. actually.

1258
00:58:42.223 --> 00:58:43.190
If I'm being honest.

1259
00:58:45.993 --> 00:58:46.961
Uh... (CHUCKLES)

1260
00:58:48.162 --> 00:58:49.163
Um...

1261
00:58:50.831 --> 00:58:51.799
Yeah.

1262
00:58:52.400 --> 00:58:53.567
I'd love that too.

1263
00:58:55.269 --> 00:58:56.070
Now. I know the place is a lot

1264
00:58:56.170 --> 00:58:57.506
but Warren's gonna give me
a bridge loan

1265
00:58:57.605 --> 00:58:58.906
and the neighborhood's
appreciating...

1266
00:58:59.006 --> 00:59:00.775
RUTH: Hey. hey.

1267
00:59:00.875 --> 00:59:03.744
I liked you when you lived
in Newark and took the bus.

1268
00:59:04.845 --> 00:59:06.113
You know that. right?

1269
00:59:09.383 --> 00:59:10.584
What?

1270
00:59:15.556 --> 00:59:16.791
Nothing.

1271
00:59:16.891 --> 00:59:21.530
By the way. I can fire you
at any time. but I won't.

1272
00:59:21.629 --> 00:59:24.765
-(ALL LAUGHING)
-(STAMMERS. CHUCKLES)

1273
00:59:24.865 --> 00:59:28.537
To continue with this story.
and he said. he's. like...

1274
00:59:28.636 --> 00:59:29.804
"What are you talking about?
Where are you?"

1275
00:59:29.904 --> 00:59:31.572
And I was. like.
"I'm in Highland Park."

1276
00:59:32.306 --> 00:59:34.842
He was. like. "No..."

1277
00:59:34.942 --> 00:59:37.378
BECKET: <i>As for the next</i>
<i>Redfellow in line.</i>

1278
00:59:37.478 --> 00:59:39.146
<i>you can probably</i>
<i>guess who it was.</i>

1279
00:59:39.246 --> 00:59:40.281
(WARREN LAUGHS)

1280
00:59:40.381 --> 00:59:42.216
BECKET: <i>But by now.</i>
<i>I couldn't imagine lifting</i>

1281
00:59:42.316 --> 00:59:44.385
<i>a finger against my uncle.</i>

1282
00:59:44.485 --> 00:59:46.887
<i>much less doing the man harm.</i>

1283
00:59:46.987 --> 00:59:50.391
And by that point. things were
going decently well.

1284
00:59:50.491 --> 00:59:53.594
The job. living situation...

1285
00:59:55.930 --> 00:59:57.264
FATHER MORRIS:
You were content.

1286
00:59:59.700 --> 01:00:02.770
Without the wealth.
Without the inheritance.

1287
01:00:06.173 --> 01:00:07.174
Well...

1288
01:00:08.109 --> 01:00:10.111
<i>Maybe you're right.</i>
<i>Maybe I was...</i>

1289
01:00:11.378 --> 01:00:12.379
<i>content.</i>

1290
01:00:13.214 --> 01:00:14.215
<i>Content enough.</i>

1291
01:00:16.350 --> 01:00:18.052
<i>And I suppose I had</i>
<i>more important things</i>

1292
01:00:18.152 --> 01:00:18.953
<i>to think about.</i>

1293
01:00:19.053 --> 01:00:21.722
RUTH: <i>My mom's gonna</i>
<i>want Zinfandel.</i>

1294
01:00:21.822 --> 01:00:23.757
I think we're making
the right choice. by the way.

1295
01:00:23.858 --> 01:00:26.561
Having an engagement party
at your home just feels.

1296
01:00:26.660 --> 01:00:30.064
better than
at a bar or something.

1297
01:00:30.631 --> 01:00:32.933
I totally agree.

1298
01:00:35.336 --> 01:00:37.037
RUTH: I'm still thinking
about your family.

1299
01:00:38.639 --> 01:00:39.840
All the crazy shit.

1300
01:00:40.674 --> 01:00:41.876
Okay.

1301
01:00:42.676 --> 01:00:43.744
I don't mean to obsess.

1302
01:00:43.844 --> 01:00:45.880
but don't you think
that it's...

1303
01:00:45.980 --> 01:00:48.282
BECKET: I'm not even
a part of that family.

1304
01:00:48.382 --> 01:00:50.251
Whatever's going on. it's got
nothing to do with us.

1305
01:00:51.520 --> 01:00:53.120
Besides. it's probably
over anyway.

1306
01:00:54.088 --> 01:00:55.289
RUTH: What makes you say that?

1307
01:00:58.859 --> 01:01:00.127
I don't know.

1308
01:01:00.494 --> 01:01:02.163
Just sayin' it.

1309
01:01:02.263 --> 01:01:04.665
-(TRAFFIC BUSTLING)
-(DISTANT SIRENS BLARING)

1310
01:01:09.170 --> 01:01:11.772
PINFIELD: Excuse me.
Mr. Redfellow?

1311
01:01:11.872 --> 01:01:13.207
Becket Redfellow?

1312
01:01:15.843 --> 01:01:17.044
How you doing today?

1313
01:01:20.649 --> 01:01:21.815
(BECKET CLEARS THROAT)

1314
01:01:24.285 --> 01:01:25.819
MATTHEWS: Nice office
you got here.

1315
01:01:27.556 --> 01:01:29.524
I like it. (CHUCKLES)

1316
01:01:29.624 --> 01:01:30.592
PINFIELD:
Just so we understand.

1317
01:01:30.691 --> 01:01:31.825
you said you're not an heir

1318
01:01:31.926 --> 01:01:33.127
to the estate.
is that correct?

1319
01:01:33.827 --> 01:01:35.530
As far as I know.

1320
01:01:35.630 --> 01:01:38.132
Well. we did
a little research. and...

1321
01:01:39.166 --> 01:01:40.167
Congratulations.

1322
01:01:52.647 --> 01:01:54.248
BECKET: Wow.

1323
01:01:54.348 --> 01:01:56.551
Uh. it's just a little...

1324
01:01:56.984 --> 01:01:58.852
I... I had no idea.

1325
01:01:58.953 --> 01:02:01.523
Hmm. Can you answer
a few questions for us?

1326
01:02:01.623 --> 01:02:02.691
Yeah. I'm... I'm sorry.

1327
01:02:02.790 --> 01:02:04.191
Um. I... I really had no idea.
This is...

1328
01:02:04.291 --> 01:02:05.826
PINFIELD: Nobody's
arguing with you.

1329
01:02:07.328 --> 01:02:08.663
MATTHEWS: Can you tell us
where you were

1330
01:02:08.762 --> 01:02:09.763
on the afternoon
of April 10th?

1331
01:02:09.863 --> 01:02:11.298
It would've been a Sunday.

1332
01:02:15.402 --> 01:02:16.403
BECKET: Oh...

1333
01:02:17.171 --> 01:02:19.674
April 10th. Okay. Here we go.

1334
01:02:19.773 --> 01:02:21.041
MATTHEWS: You're
fucking kidding me.

1335
01:02:22.109 --> 01:02:24.613
He remembers when
and where he bought a hot dog.

1336
01:02:24.713 --> 01:02:26.013
Is that even him?

1337
01:02:26.347 --> 01:02:27.649
I don't know.

1338
01:02:27.748 --> 01:02:28.916
Can you see who it is?

1339
01:02:30.985 --> 01:02:33.454
PINFIELD: I can't see shit.
MATTHEWS: Me neither.

1340
01:02:33.555 --> 01:02:34.922
PINFIELD: All right.
follow him.

1341
01:02:35.022 --> 01:02:37.791
WOMAN: Rothburn's going down.
and Bellman's gonna go too.

1342
01:02:37.891 --> 01:02:39.360
They're minutes away.
I guarantee it.

1343
01:02:39.460 --> 01:02:41.428
MAN: I say we dump
whatever we can cut loose

1344
01:02:41.529 --> 01:02:42.597
before the markets catch wind.

1345
01:02:42.697 --> 01:02:45.799
WOMAN: We can say we were
forced into it. which is true.

1346
01:02:46.400 --> 01:02:47.368
No.

1347
01:02:49.303 --> 01:02:50.271
I spent 35 years

1348
01:02:50.371 --> 01:02:52.540
earning the trust
of these shareholders.

1349
01:02:53.807 --> 01:02:55.276
I'm not throwing them
to the sharks

1350
01:02:55.376 --> 01:02:56.443
in one afternoon.

1351
01:02:56.544 --> 01:02:58.546
(CELLPHONE RINGING)

1352
01:03:00.814 --> 01:03:03.050
-Oh. shit.
-BECKET: What?

1353
01:03:03.150 --> 01:03:04.785
(WARREN EXHALES DEEPLY)

1354
01:03:08.822 --> 01:03:11.292
-Goddamn! (GRUNTING)
-Oh. whoa. Oh. oh. oh!

1355
01:03:14.161 --> 01:03:16.063
-(GASPING)
-MAN: Is he all right?

1356
01:03:17.998 --> 01:03:19.500
-Becket...
-Call an ambulance!

1357
01:03:24.305 --> 01:03:26.373
WARREN: <i>Pass me that water.</i>
<i>will ya?</i>

1358
01:03:27.474 --> 01:03:29.443
(GRUNTS. GULPING)

1359
01:03:33.480 --> 01:03:35.316
(EXHALES. SIGHS)

1360
01:03:37.251 --> 01:03:38.720
(CHUCKLES)

1361
01:03:38.819 --> 01:03:40.954
Listen. I'm not
gonna mince words.

1362
01:03:44.091 --> 01:03:46.293
You want to chase that rabbit
down the hole. huh?

1363
01:03:47.562 --> 01:03:49.531
Okay. That money rabbit.

1364
01:03:50.964 --> 01:03:52.466
Everybody loves a good chase.

1365
01:03:55.603 --> 01:03:56.837
And you're good at it.

1366
01:03:58.839 --> 01:04:00.174
But here I am.

1367
01:04:01.008 --> 01:04:02.577
61 years old and...

1368
01:04:05.145 --> 01:04:07.448
you're the only visitor
I've had all day.

1369
01:04:11.553 --> 01:04:14.121
Go find that person
in your life. Becket.

1370
01:04:16.658 --> 01:04:17.625
Whoever it is.

1371
01:04:19.426 --> 01:04:20.528
Work at loving them.

1372
01:04:22.963 --> 01:04:24.566
I mean. really work.

1373
01:04:26.967 --> 01:04:28.168
'Cause...

1374
01:04:28.869 --> 01:04:30.104
at the end of the day...

1375
01:04:31.740 --> 01:04:33.273
it's the only job that pays.

1376
01:04:40.013 --> 01:04:42.015
(DUCKS QUACKING)

1377
01:04:42.116 --> 01:04:44.118
(CHORAL MUSIC PLAYING)

1378
01:04:50.391 --> 01:04:51.925
BECKET: <i>It was in this</i>
<i>unhappy moment</i>

1379
01:04:52.025 --> 01:04:54.261
<i>that I realized</i>
<i>an ironic truth.</i>

1380
01:04:56.029 --> 01:04:57.464
<i>There is only one left.</i>

1381
01:04:58.966 --> 01:05:00.501
MAN: You can either
get rid of it.

1382
01:05:00.602 --> 01:05:02.202
or do what you like.

1383
01:05:04.972 --> 01:05:06.340
But not here.

1384
01:05:08.142 --> 01:05:09.577
Not under this roof.

1385
01:05:13.648 --> 01:05:16.316
And I think you know
I have to stand by that.

1386
01:05:18.720 --> 01:05:20.254
A man of my word.

1387
01:05:21.422 --> 01:05:23.424
BECKET: <i>One left.</i>

1388
01:05:24.491 --> 01:05:26.126
<i>But what use was it</i>
<i>to fantasize?</i>

1389
01:05:26.226 --> 01:05:28.730
<i>I had put all that behind me.</i>

1390
01:05:28.830 --> 01:05:31.231
Hey. Becket. Letter for you.

1391
01:05:31.965 --> 01:05:33.167
-Thanks. Brian.
-Yep.

1392
01:05:41.175 --> 01:05:42.943
(CHORAL MUSIC CONTINUES)

1393
01:05:46.848 --> 01:05:48.382
-(MUSIC STOPS)
-(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

1394
01:05:49.751 --> 01:05:51.485
-Hey.
-He invited me.

1395
01:05:51.586 --> 01:05:52.587
RUTH: (OVER PHONE) <i>What?</i>

1396
01:05:53.187 --> 01:05:55.155
My grandfather.

1397
01:05:55.255 --> 01:05:58.058
To a dinner party
at the estate. (CHUCKLES)

1398
01:05:59.126 --> 01:06:01.128
- <i>Hello?</i>
-Uh. I just...

1399
01:06:01.228 --> 01:06:03.598
I... I thought you said
you would never do that?

1400
01:06:03.698 --> 01:06:05.132
-Never do what?
-RUTH: <i>Never meet the guy.</i>

1401
01:06:05.232 --> 01:06:06.634
<i>Wait. when is this?</i>

1402
01:06:06.734 --> 01:06:08.636
-Tonight.
- <i>It's Friday.</i>

1403
01:06:08.736 --> 01:06:10.471
-BECKET: I know.
-Friday.

1404
01:06:10.839 --> 01:06:12.239
BECKET: <i>Oh. shit.</i>

1405
01:06:12.339 --> 01:06:16.109
Ruth. I may not have
this opportunity again.

1406
01:06:16.210 --> 01:06:17.377
He never sees anyone.

1407
01:06:17.478 --> 01:06:19.346
RUTH: <i>You may not have</i>
<i>this opportunity again?</i>

1408
01:06:19.446 --> 01:06:21.048
-I don't know.
- <i>Yeah. you're right.</i>

1409
01:06:21.148 --> 01:06:22.382
So be home by 7:00
or you will miss

1410
01:06:22.483 --> 01:06:25.319
your own fucking engagement
party. like... (SCOFFS)

1411
01:06:25.419 --> 01:06:27.722
Right. Of course. Of course.

1412
01:06:29.022 --> 01:06:30.525
Okay.

1413
01:06:30.625 --> 01:06:32.159
I love you. by the way.

1414
01:06:36.263 --> 01:06:37.464
I'm gonna call you back.

1415
01:06:39.834 --> 01:06:41.536
Package for Mr. Redfellow.

1416
01:06:55.583 --> 01:06:56.551
Remember to breathe.

1417
01:06:57.585 --> 01:06:58.553
Very important.

1418
01:06:59.988 --> 01:07:01.623
