01:23:00.013 --> 01:23:01.181
I'll give you
the full explanation.

1659
01:23:01.281 --> 01:23:03.050
You're withholding
something from me.

1660
01:23:04.251 --> 01:23:06.453
You've been withholding
something from me.

1661
01:23:07.421 --> 01:23:08.556
(SIGHS)

1662
01:23:08.923 --> 01:23:10.290
So right now...

1663
01:23:12.292 --> 01:23:14.061
you have to tell me
what's up...

1664
01:23:15.530 --> 01:23:16.497
or I'm out.

1665
01:23:22.837 --> 01:23:24.004
(EXHALES)

1666
01:23:28.910 --> 01:23:30.177
(SIGHS)

1667
01:23:30.277 --> 01:23:32.479
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

1668
01:23:38.953 --> 01:23:42.422
BECKET: <i>Sometimes in life.</i>
<i>you gotta take a deep breath.</i>

1669
01:23:42.524 --> 01:23:45.058
<i>come clean</i>
<i>to the person you love.</i>

1670
01:23:48.061 --> 01:23:51.533
<i>This was not</i>
<i>one of those times.</i>

1671
01:23:51.633 --> 01:23:53.300
<i>I only told her</i>
<i>what she'd see on the news.</i>

1672
01:23:53.400 --> 01:23:55.035
NEWS REPORTER: <i>... is indeed</i>
<i>dead. and it seems...</i>

1673
01:23:55.135 --> 01:23:56.270
BECKET:
<i>My grandfather was gone.</i>

1674
01:23:56.370 --> 01:23:57.839
NEWS REPORTER:
<i>...some sort of altercation...</i>

1675
01:23:57.939 --> 01:23:59.674
BECKET:
<i>And as for the fortune.</i>

1676
01:24:00.708 --> 01:24:01.676
<i>well...</i>

1677
01:24:01.776 --> 01:24:03.511
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

1678
01:24:17.959 --> 01:24:19.159
(SIGHS)

1679
01:24:24.131 --> 01:24:26.500
-(ALL APPLAUDING)
-(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

1680
01:24:51.258 --> 01:24:52.727
BECKET: <i>The right kind</i>
<i>of life.</i>

1681
01:24:53.528 --> 01:24:55.362
<i>This had to be it. right?</i>

1682
01:24:57.464 --> 01:24:58.866
<i>Sure. she had</i>
<i>a few misgivings.</i>

1683
01:24:58.967 --> 01:25:01.569
<i>but we can handle that later.</i>

1684
01:25:03.103 --> 01:25:06.106
<i>For now. I was rich.</i>

1685
01:25:06.206 --> 01:25:08.208
<i>And being rich</i>

1686
01:25:08.308 --> 01:25:10.645
<i>is even better</i>
<i>than you imagine.</i>

1687
01:25:11.879 --> 01:25:13.581
(MUSIC CONCLUDES)

1688
01:25:16.918 --> 01:25:19.587
(CLOCK TICKING)

1689
01:25:20.888 --> 01:25:23.691
You know I mentioned earlier.
this is a tragedy.

1690
01:25:25.994 --> 01:25:27.194
Still is.

1691
01:25:28.328 --> 01:25:30.430
-Donald Macnamara. my wife.
-Hello.

1692
01:25:30.531 --> 01:25:31.699
-Such a pleasure.
-Nice to meet you.

1693
01:25:31.799 --> 01:25:33.467
Nice to meet you.

1694
01:25:33.568 --> 01:25:36.871
-RUTH: Hi.
-Nancy Dillard. the Dillards.

1695
01:25:36.971 --> 01:25:38.372
-Nice to meet you.
-NANCY: Mmm-hmm.

1696
01:25:39.073 --> 01:25:40.340
Megan Pinfield.

1697
01:25:40.440 --> 01:25:41.509
FBI.

1698
01:25:42.242 --> 01:25:43.544
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1699
01:25:44.746 --> 01:25:45.713
Hello.

1700
01:25:49.684 --> 01:25:51.719
Can you shut that door
behind you. please?

1701
01:25:53.286 --> 01:25:54.454
(BECKET SIGHS)

1702
01:25:57.592 --> 01:26:01.361
Look. not to be uncouth.
but this is...

1703
01:26:01.461 --> 01:26:02.396
heroically bad timing.

1704
01:26:02.496 --> 01:26:04.032
Yeah. you're under arrest.

1705
01:26:04.132 --> 01:26:05.499
I need you to stay calm
and cooperate.

1706
01:26:05.600 --> 01:26:08.903
-I'm under arrest? For what?
-For murder.

1707
01:26:11.506 --> 01:26:12.573
Of who?

1708
01:26:13.875 --> 01:26:15.308
Lyle Archdale.

1709
01:26:16.811 --> 01:26:19.246
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

1710
01:26:24.451 --> 01:26:25.620
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

1711
01:26:29.057 --> 01:26:30.625
RUTH: Hey. wait!

1712
01:26:32.426 --> 01:26:34.361
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1713
01:26:35.830 --> 01:26:37.230
RUTH: What do we do?

1714
01:26:37.799 --> 01:26:38.766
What do we do?

1715
01:26:39.399 --> 01:26:40.902
(ENGINE ROARING)

1716
01:26:41.803 --> 01:26:43.236
Ruth. I love...

1717
01:26:44.972 --> 01:26:47.240
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

1718
01:27:01.122 --> 01:27:02.590
BECKET: <i>Can you believe it?</i>

1719
01:27:03.991 --> 01:27:05.026
<i>After all this.</i>

1720
01:27:05.126 --> 01:27:06.994
<i>I'd go down for a killing</i>
<i>I didn't even commit.</i>

1721
01:27:07.095 --> 01:27:08.495
NEWS REPORTER: <i>Now we wanna</i>
<i>point out to listeners</i>

1722
01:27:08.596 --> 01:27:10.965
<i>that Becket Redfellow</i>
<i>crossed state lines.</i>

1723
01:27:11.065 --> 01:27:13.801
<i>which is why his trial</i>
<i>is unfolding in federal court</i>

1724
01:27:13.901 --> 01:27:16.436
<i>where murder can still mean</i>
<i>capital punishment</i>

1725
01:27:16.537 --> 01:27:18.773
<i>for citizens of New Jersey.</i>

1726
01:27:18.873 --> 01:27:22.342
As we can see
from these security tapes.

1727
01:27:22.442 --> 01:27:24.244
Mr. Redfellow
burst into the office

1728
01:27:24.344 --> 01:27:26.714
at approximately 5:03 p.m..

1729
01:27:26.814 --> 01:27:29.784
and then emerged
just four minutes later.

1730
01:27:29.884 --> 01:27:31.886
which is consistent
with the estimated time

1731
01:27:31.986 --> 01:27:33.621
of Mr. Archdale's death.

1732
01:27:34.555 --> 01:27:37.324
Now. we've heard
from the coroner

1733
01:27:37.424 --> 01:27:39.160
that he estimates
the time of death

1734
01:27:39.259 --> 01:27:41.729
between 5:06 and 5:15 p.m.

1735
01:27:42.230 --> 01:27:43.197
And we've heard

1736
01:27:43.296 --> 01:27:44.799
from the eyewitness
in the hallway.

1737
01:27:44.899 --> 01:27:48.435
who positively identifies
Mr. Redfellow.

1738
01:27:48.536 --> 01:27:51.105
Sir. can you confirm that
this is the murder weapon?

1739
01:27:51.205 --> 01:27:53.406
Uh. I can confirm
that it is. yes.

1740
01:27:53.508 --> 01:27:54.474
And did you find
the defendant's fingerprints

1741
01:27:54.575 --> 01:27:55.610
on the murder weapon?

1742
01:27:55.710 --> 01:27:57.011
FORENSICS EXPERT:
I did. yes.

1743
01:27:57.111 --> 01:27:59.747
How certain are you that. uh.
these are his fingerprints?

1744
01:27:59.847 --> 01:28:01.082
FORENSICS EXPERT:
I'm 100% certain.

1745
01:28:01.182 --> 01:28:02.349
BECKET: <i>A letter opener.</i>

1746
01:28:05.485 --> 01:28:08.421
My entire life
because of a letter opener.

1747
01:28:08.523 --> 01:28:11.559
PROSECUTOR: You were the first
to find your husband's body.

1748
01:28:12.026 --> 01:28:13.161
Is that correct?

1749
01:28:13.261 --> 01:28:14.862
Yes.

1750
01:28:14.962 --> 01:28:18.933
Tell me. Were you in love with
Mr. Redfellow at the time?

1751
01:28:19.033 --> 01:28:20.034
(JULIA SNIFFLES)

1752
01:28:21.102 --> 01:28:22.603
Yes. (CRYING)

1753
01:28:22.703 --> 01:28:24.639
PROSECUTOR:
And he with you?

1754
01:28:30.611 --> 01:28:33.147
Becket Redfellow
has been in love with me

1755
01:28:33.681 --> 01:28:36.017
his entire life. (SNIFFLES)

1756
01:28:36.818 --> 01:28:37.919
(JULIA SOBBING)

1757
01:28:38.019 --> 01:28:40.922
I just never thought he would
do something like this.

1758
01:28:41.022 --> 01:28:43.024
(SOBBING)

1759
01:28:44.258 --> 01:28:45.560
I'm sorry.

1760
01:28:46.661 --> 01:28:48.328
JUDGE: <i>Will the defense</i>
<i>please rise?</i>

1761
01:28:50.363 --> 01:28:51.464
Upon the verdict.

1762
01:28:51.566 --> 01:28:54.302
the jury finds the defendant.
Becket Redfellow.

1763
01:28:54.401 --> 01:28:56.604
guilty of murder
in the first degree

1764
01:28:56.704 --> 01:28:58.105
as charged in the indictment

1765
01:28:58.206 --> 01:28:59.472
and that
the punishment of death

1766
01:28:59.574 --> 01:29:00.741
-shall be imposed.
-(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

1767
01:29:00.842 --> 01:29:02.944
JUDGE: May the sentence
be recorded by the clerk.

1768
01:29:03.044 --> 01:29:04.779
May God rest his soul.

1769
01:29:04.879 --> 01:29:06.047
Thank you.

1770
01:29:06.147 --> 01:29:07.515
(GAVEL BANGS)

1771
01:29:08.816 --> 01:29:10.685
BECKET: <i>I wish I could find</i>
<i>the right words</i>

1772
01:29:10.785 --> 01:29:12.920
<i>to describe this juncture</i>
<i>in my story.</i>

1773
01:29:14.487 --> 01:29:16.123
(DOOR BUZZING)

1774
01:29:16.791 --> 01:29:17.658
(DOOR SLAMS)

1775
01:29:17.758 --> 01:29:20.061
PRISON GUARD: Cell 15. secure!

1776
01:29:23.865 --> 01:29:26.033
BECKET: <i>But there are</i>
<i>no right words.</i>

1777
01:29:28.269 --> 01:29:29.237
(EXHALES)

1778
01:29:29.337 --> 01:29:30.738
<i>There's only time.</i>

1779
01:29:32.740 --> 01:29:34.842
<i>-And silence.</i>
<i>-</i> (CLOCK TICKING)

1780
01:29:36.878 --> 01:29:38.880
(CLOCK TICKING)

1781
01:29:44.118 --> 01:29:46.120
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1782
01:29:51.259 --> 01:29:52.660
(FOOTSTEPS HALT)

1783
01:29:52.760 --> 01:29:54.028
-PRISON GUARD: Yo.
-(THUMPING ON RAILS)

1784
01:29:54.128 --> 01:29:55.930
You got a visitor.

1785
01:30:05.706 --> 01:30:07.575
PRISON GUARD:
You got three minutes.

1786
01:30:08.876 --> 01:30:09.877
(BECKET SIGHS)

1787
01:30:23.423 --> 01:30:24.592
(INHALES)

1788
01:30:26.794 --> 01:30:29.462
You must be quite the catch
back there.

1789
01:30:35.336 --> 01:30:37.038
You got a big day
coming up. huh?

1790
01:30:39.707 --> 01:30:42.076
You remember that game
we used to play as kids?

1791
01:30:43.344 --> 01:30:44.946
I'd have a secret. and...

1792
01:30:45.880 --> 01:30:46.948
you'd try to guess
what it was.

1793
01:30:47.048 --> 01:30:48.582
If you've got
something to say. say it.

1794
01:30:51.252 --> 01:30:52.987
All right.
I'll give you a hint.

1795
01:30:54.055 --> 01:30:56.590
-It involves handwriting.
-You're foul.

1796
01:30:58.626 --> 01:31:01.195
You're a lump of coal
with makeup.

1797
01:31:03.496 --> 01:31:05.700
I'd rather die in here
than be with you.

1798
01:31:08.536 --> 01:31:10.004
I'll give you another hint.

1799
01:31:10.104 --> 01:31:11.238
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1800
01:31:12.807 --> 01:31:13.774
Lyle...

1801
01:31:15.343 --> 01:31:17.078
when I found him like that...

1802
01:31:18.679 --> 01:31:20.748
I found something else. too.

1803
01:31:21.615 --> 01:31:23.317
And beautifully written.
I might add.

1804
01:31:23.751 --> 01:31:24.752
What's with the white?

1805
01:31:24.852 --> 01:31:26.520
Are you boys playing doctor
back there?

1806
01:31:26.620 --> 01:31:27.922
Did Lyle leave a note?

1807
01:31:28.022 --> 01:31:30.691
Is that what you're saying?
Did Lyle leave a note?

1808
01:31:32.126 --> 01:31:33.694
-JULIA: You know...
-If Lyle wrote a note...

1809
01:31:33.794 --> 01:31:34.996
-I think I might just leave...
-If that's what you're saying.

1810
01:31:35.096 --> 01:31:36.263
in the name
of all things holy.

1811
01:31:36.364 --> 01:31:37.665
you have to release it.

1812
01:31:40.267 --> 01:31:41.969
-Oh. now you want to talk?
-What do you want?

1813
01:31:42.069 --> 01:31:43.537
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

1814
01:31:43.637 --> 01:31:45.906
-What do you want?
-Becket...

1815
01:31:46.007 --> 01:31:48.275
What could you possibly have
to offer?

1816
01:31:49.477 --> 01:31:51.912
No. no. no. no. no!
Hey. hey. hey! Stop!

1817
01:31:52.013 --> 01:31:54.382
-That's it! (GRUNTING)
-Tell me! Stop! Stop!

1818
01:31:54.482 --> 01:31:55.783
I have 30 seconds!

1819
01:31:55.883 --> 01:31:57.418
-PRISON GUARD: You got 25.
-Okay.

1820
01:31:57.518 --> 01:31:59.820
-Sit down.
-Julia!

1821
01:31:59.920 --> 01:32:02.023
Julia. come here. please!
Please!

1822
01:32:02.123 --> 01:32:03.691
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1823
01:32:06.861 --> 01:32:07.862
Okay.

1824
01:32:12.733 --> 01:32:13.934
What do you want?

1825
01:32:19.006 --> 01:32:20.875
-Just give me a moment.
-(SLAMS FIST)

1826
01:32:23.344 --> 01:32:25.046
I'm gonna die in 24 hours.

1827
01:32:25.813 --> 01:32:27.081
You don't want that to happen.

1828
01:32:27.181 --> 01:32:29.250
I know you don't want that
to happen.

1829
01:32:30.785 --> 01:32:32.953
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1830
01:32:36.590 --> 01:32:37.925
Give me everything.

1831
01:32:40.928 --> 01:32:42.897
-Sign it over to...
-(LINE DISCONNECTS)

1832
01:32:56.210 --> 01:32:57.912
(ALARM BUZZING)

1833
01:32:58.012 --> 01:32:59.180
(THUDS)

1834
01:33:03.584 --> 01:33:05.086
(EXHALES)

1835
01:33:11.759 --> 01:33:13.661
PRISON GUARD:
You need anything else?

1836
01:33:15.329 --> 01:33:16.831
Got a priest?

1837
01:33:19.400 --> 01:33:21.202
Well. that was some hours ago.

1838
01:33:22.603 --> 01:33:23.671
And if you're curious

1839
01:33:23.771 --> 01:33:27.576
why I've been so calm
and self-assured

1840
01:33:27.675 --> 01:33:29.777
for a man
set to be executed in...

1841
01:33:33.147 --> 01:33:37.351
it's because I thought
our friend Julia. might. uh...

1842
01:33:39.887 --> 01:33:42.356
might come through in the end.

1843
01:33:43.624 --> 01:33:44.859
(INHALES)

1844
01:33:49.598 --> 01:33:50.898
I wonder if she's coming.

1845
01:34:01.809 --> 01:34:03.512
FATHER MORRIS:
"The Lord is my shepherd

1846
01:34:03.911 --> 01:34:05.279
"I shall not want.

1847
01:34:06.280 --> 01:34:09.083
"He maketh me to lie down
in green pastures.

1848
01:34:10.117 --> 01:34:12.587
"He leadeth me
beside the still waters."

1849
01:34:12.686 --> 01:34:14.121
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

1850
01:34:14.221 --> 01:34:16.690
"He restoreth my soul.

1851
01:34:16.790 --> 01:34:18.593
"He leadeth me
in the paths of righteousness

1852
01:34:18.692 --> 01:34:20.161
"for his name's sake.

1853
01:34:21.061 --> 01:34:22.096
"Yea. though I walk through

1854
01:34:22.196 --> 01:34:23.598
"the valley
of the shadow of death

1855
01:34:23.697 --> 01:34:25.432
"I will fear no evil

1856
01:34:26.267 --> 01:34:27.668
"for thou art with me.

1857
01:34:28.769 --> 01:34:31.405
"Thy rod and thy staff
they comfort me."

1858
01:34:31.505 --> 01:34:32.607
(CLOCK TICKING)

1859
01:34:32.706 --> 01:34:36.377
(FATHER MORRIS CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY)

1860
01:34:38.679 --> 01:34:39.980
PRISON GUARD: Redfellow.

1861
01:34:41.650 --> 01:34:43.684
You're not gonna
fuckin' believe this.

1862
01:34:45.252 --> 01:34:46.854
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1863
01:34:46.954 --> 01:34:48.088
POLICE CHIEF:
First and foremost.

1864
01:34:48.189 --> 01:34:50.891
we have absolute faith
in our forensic team...

1865
01:34:50.991 --> 01:34:54.795
(CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)

1866
01:35:01.335 --> 01:35:02.336
PRISON GUARD: <i>Open 15.</i>

1867
01:35:02.937 --> 01:35:04.505
(DOOR SLIDING OPEN)

1868
01:35:04.606 --> 01:35:05.806
Let's go.

1869
01:35:08.677 --> 01:35:10.911
(DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

1870
01:35:14.649 --> 01:35:15.816
(RUSTLING)

1871
01:35:16.450 --> 01:35:18.485
(DOOR BUZZING)

1872
01:35:32.567 --> 01:35:33.867
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

1873
01:35:46.615 --> 01:35:47.815
(SIGHS)

1874
01:35:48.415 --> 01:35:49.383
BECKET: You came.

1875
01:36:01.028 --> 01:36:02.796
(CAR DOOR CLOSES.
ENGINE STARTS)

1876
01:36:04.666 --> 01:36:05.933
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1877
01:36:06.033 --> 01:36:07.801
(ENGINE ACCELERATING)

1878
01:36:22.816 --> 01:36:24.351
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

1879
01:36:36.765 --> 01:36:37.766
(LATIN POP MUSIC PLAYING)

1880
01:36:37.865 --> 01:36:39.066
(SIGHS)

1881
01:36:46.340 --> 01:36:47.341
(SIGHS)

1882
01:36:50.779 --> 01:36:51.979
All right.

1883
01:37:08.996 --> 01:37:11.131
(MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING)

1884
01:37:19.340 --> 01:37:21.975
FEMALE CHORUS:
♪ <i>Hey. hey. dee-dee</i> ♪

1885
01:37:22.076 --> 01:37:24.813
♪ <i>Take me back to Piauí</i> ♪

1886
01:37:24.912 --> 01:37:27.147
♪ <i>Hey. hey. dee-dee</i> ♪

1887
01:37:27.247 --> 01:37:29.983
♪ <i>Take me back to Piauí</i> ♪

1888
01:37:30.084 --> 01:37:32.620
♪ <i>Hey. hey. dee-dee</i> ♪

1889
01:37:32.721 --> 01:37:34.823
♪ <i>Take me back to Piauí</i> ♪

1890
01:37:34.922 --> 01:37:37.559
BECKET: <i>I told you</i>
<i>this is a tragedy.</i>

1891
01:37:37.659 --> 01:37:39.426
<i>It's not about me. is it?</i>

1892
01:37:40.227 --> 01:37:41.563
<i>I think it's about you.</i>

1893
01:37:41.663 --> 01:37:46.266
<i>with all your values</i>
<i>and deep-rooted expectations.</i>

1894
01:37:48.837 --> 01:37:51.038
<i>You thought this would end</i>
<i>differently.</i>

1895
01:37:51.573 --> 01:37:53.340
<i>And in a perfect universe.</i>

1896
